I am 16 years old and I have been depressed for about a year and a half and have been on antidepressants for a year. Antidepressants DO NOT cure depression. They simply take the edge off the weight of the emotions. It just makes you feel a bit lighter emotionally and that you actually have a shot at life. I do recommend them and personally I recommend taking them and seeing a psychologist together as the pills won‚Äôt solve your problems.

I have been to many psychologists but none of them have really changed my life completely or hit the nail on the head. If you aren‚Äôt the type of person to just sit down and talk then I suggest some sort of therapy like art therapy as it helped me become calm and easier to explain my emotions in more than just talking.

What has really helped me of late is this type of therapy called TRE which stands for trauma release exercise which is really different and weird but it makes you feel like a new person after each session and really brings some calmness and happiness to your life.

I‚Äôm really open to having a conversation if you need some help so message me for more info üòä
